        <mxCell id="n-e7-label" parent="1" style="text;html=1;align=center;fontSize=11;fontStyle=2;strokeColor=none;fillColor=#FFFFFF" value="agent_turn events + tool calls + (eventually) task_completed" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="20" width="340" x="1965" y="1044" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ad5-box" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFF3E0;strokeColor=#EF6C00;fontSize=11;align=left;spacing=8;spacingLeft=10;fontStyle=0" value="AD-5 rationale — why combined-turn ack&#xa;&#xa;The Claude Agent SDK does NOT expose a mid-conversation context-injection API:&#xa;— HookEvent enum is fixed (no custom events)&#xa;— ClaudeAgentOptions.system_prompt is construction-time only&#xa;— hookSpecificOutput.additionalContext is user-visible-only (Anthropic not-planned)&#xa;&#xa;The Stop/between-turns hook is the only surface; decision:&quot;block&quot; burns exactly one turn.&#xa;We ack BEFORE returning so the user sees nudge_acknowledged via watch/Slack&#xa;even if the subsequent turn takes minutes. Cost is surfaced honestly — the alternative&#xa;(silent multi-turn overhead) would be an operator trap." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="250" width="1400" x="120" y="1100" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="legend-key" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#E8EAF6;strokeColor=#3F51B5;fontSize=11;align=left;spacing=8;spacingLeft=10;fontFamily=Courier New" value="Ordered steps&#xa;1  CLI POST /nudge (durable)&#xa;2  NudgeFn: rate-limit + PutItem + 202&#xa;3  Between-turns hook reads pending&#xa;4  Emit nudge_acknowledged event (BEFORE returning — AD-5)&#xa;5  Mark nudge consumed (idempotent)&#xa;6  Return decision:&quot;block&quot; with nudge text — SDK treats as user turn" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="170" width="780" x="1540" y="1100" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
