        <mxCell id="f-defaults" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFF8E1;strokeColor=#F57F17;fontSize=11;align=left;spacing=8;spacingLeft=10;fontFamily=Courier New" value="Per-channel default filters (v1 — AD-4, §6.2)&#xa;&#xa;     Channel      │ Default subscribed events                                                │ --verbose adds&#xa;     ─────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼──────────────────&#xa;     Slack        │ task_completed, task_failed, task_cancelled, pr_created, agent_error,    │ agent_milestone&#xa;                  │ approval_required, status_response                                        │&#xa;     Email        │ task_completed, task_failed, approval_required                            │ —&#xa;     GitHub       │ pr_created + terminal status (edit-in-place single comment)              │ — already minimal&#xa;&#xa;agent_milestone unwrap (effectiveEventType): router unwraps agent_milestone events whose&#xa;metadata.milestone is in the narrow allowlist (today: {pr_created}) to the underlying name before&#xa;matching channel filters. Unlisted milestone names stay wrapped and do not route. The watch CLI&#xa;renders all milestones regardless of this allowlist.&#xa;Numeric coercion: DDB returns Number attributes as strings — dispatcher coerces cost_usd /&#xa;duration_s via a shared helper before calling renderCommentBody.&#xa;&#xa;Rationale: if Slack pings on every milestone, users mute the bot within days. Default to the minimal&#xa;set that surfaces decision-requiring events + completion; power users opt into verbose streams." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="320" width="1700" x="100" y="470" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="f-gh-title" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=14;fontStyle=1" value="GitHub edit-in-place — single-shot PATCH, DDB-Stream ordering (AD-9, §6.4)&#xa;One comment per task, edited in place. No GET round-trip, no If-Match, no 412. ETag/If-Match was rejected by GitHub&#39;s API (400); see §6.4 AD-9." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="2240" x="100" y="820" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
